“Obliged, Margrie,” he murmured.
Margrie never tried to cheat him of his pay in whatever form it came.
Tonight’s was in board and lodging. Tomorrow,
he’d move on, up towards Green Haven,
where he might get paid in slightly used boots,
or a good whetstone, or maybe even a new blanket.
He played life by ear, did Harrow, taking what came his way, leaving what stood in it.
